Class MechSubstructSearch

  • java.lang.Object

      • terminiMatch

        private boolean terminiMatch(MechFlow authFlow,
                             MechFlow respFlow,
                             boolean isSrc)
        Given sinks or sources (termini) of electron-flow arrows from the author and response, do they match?

        First get a list indices of the atoms for both termini.
        Next translate the author's indices into terms of the student's indices using the searchResult as a map.
        Finally, check to see that all the values in the translated list are exist in the student's list.

        EXAMPLE: Say this example IS A MATCH, both are sources which are bonds. The numbers in square brackets are the atom Indices within their respective molecules. The ?'s in the result just mean we don't care what they are for this example (we are SURE they are not 9 or 12, since there can be no repeates in the result). We are only interested in the two atoms involved in the source of each.

        GIVEN:
        Author Structure: C[2] ------ Si[0] (authTerm, bond is source)
        Response Structure: C[9] ------ Si[12] (respTerm, bond is source)
        searchResult = [12,?,9,?,?,?,...] (means authAtom[0] matches studentAtom[12], and authAtom[2] matches studentAtom[9], the result of the last MolSearch.find)

        CALCULATE:
        authList = [0,2] (indices of pertinent atoms in stud. mol.)
        respList = [9,12] (indices of pertinent atoms in auth. mol.)
        transList = [2,0] (respList[] mapped/translated using searchResult[])

        So YES the transList[] contains the same values as the authList[], therefore these two sources are a match!

        Parameters:
        authFlow - the author's electron-flow arrow
        respFlow - the response's electron-flow arrow
        isSrc - true if we are looking at sources
        Returns:
        true if they match

      • getTerminusAtomIndices

        private int[] getTerminusAtomIndices(Molecule mol,
                                     MechFlow flow,
                                     boolean getSrc)
        Gets the atom indices of an electron-flow arrow sink or source. A sink or source is made up of one or two atoms, so the returned value will be of length 1 or 2. Example: if the source (or sink) is a bond between a Carbon with index 15 and a Bromine with index 33, returns [15,33] or [33,15] (no order guaranteed).
        Parameters:
        mol - a molecule
        flow - an electron-flow arrow
        getSrc - true if should get the source atoms
        Returns:
        array of ints representing the index or indices of the atoms of the sink or source
